<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="31c3ad29-9d33-5ec6-a934-d887bc3b2dcb" activityNameId="7301357f-f8cd-42f8-88ce-9b0d073f4201" parentActivityId="bb020e82-07c7-4bfe-b9a6-6809cd7aec32" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">rice production, non-basmati</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">This activity starts about seven weeks after the harvest of the previous crop. The soil is prepared for cultivation in June and sowing of seeds started about three weeks after soil preparation. Thereafter the crop is mature for harvesting in about 4.5 months.
</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the harvesting of the matured non-basmati rice plant. Thereafter the field is prepared for cultivation of the next crop.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of Rice Non-Basmati during June-October, 2016 at a farm located in village Village-Gadhera, District- Fatehgarh Sahib of Punjab. In this area, fields are irrigated using electric pump and diesel pump from groundwater for surface irrigation. The farm has a yield of 7750 kg fresh matter per ha for this crop cycle. Sowing date for the crop is 20- June, 2016 and harvesting date is 31-October, 2016. Mineral NP fertilizer input is 84.77-48.53 kg/ha. Herbicides used has active ingredient as Butachlor 1250g/ha (for which Alachlor has been used as proxy). Fungicides used has active ingredients as Propiconazole 156.25g/ha, Insecticides used has active ingredient Chlorpyriphos 125g/ha, Monocrotophos 450g/ha (for which Dichlorovos has been used as proxy), and Cartap Hydrochloride 8750g/ha (for which Carbosulfan has been used as proxy). Machinery is used for soil cultivation with fuel consumption of 43.68 kg/ha using plough, rotary cultivator for soil tillage and for other works. Machines is used for harvesting with fuel consumption of 78kg/ha using Threshing for combine harvesting and hay reaping. For other work process 7.1136 kg/ha is used for laser levelling. </text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="a2cfa5cb-7e0a-4b16-88d6-75bececda629">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">0112:Growing of rice</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0e6a7860-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">IN</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">village Village-Gadhera, District- Fatehgarh Sahib of Punjab</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Cultivation of Non-Basmati Rice follows conventional production standards</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2015-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Soil cultivating date for the main crop: 01-June, 2016; Harvesting date main crop: 31-October, 2016. The soil cultivation, sowing and harvesting dates are taken as the middle date of the week or fortnight told to the data collector by the farmer. Total time from date of sowing to date of harvesting comes to 130 days.  The data is collected for one crop cycle. The cycle of one year is considered for entry in ecoeditor.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
