        <name xml:lang="en">irrigation</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m3</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The total water (blue + green) used for the production of 1 kg of paddy rice in India is 1.903 m3, where blue water is 0.826 m3 and green water is 1.077 m3. For irrigation only blue water is considered. Therefore, 0.826 m3/kg paddy rice.
Source: Chapagain, A.K., Hoekstra, A.Y. (2010). The green, blue and grey water footprint of rice from both a production and consumption perspective. Value of Water Research Report Series No. 40. Accessed on 20231020: https://www.waterfootprint.org/resources/Report40-WaterFootprintRice.pdf</comment>
