      <parameter parameterId="df700e91-4922-4ad9-b7cc-ba7d8ddd7a85" amount="1.0" variableName="LUC_crop_specific" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
        <name xml:lang="en">LUC_crop_specific</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">This parameter allows to switch between a "crop specific" and a "country specific" approach when calculating the LUC of a crop. By default, the chosen approach is "crop specific", so the value of the parameter is 1. If you want to apply a "country specific" approach, turn the parameter to 0.</comment>
      </parameter>
    </flowData>
    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">The farmers were identified and contacted by agriculture science faculty familiar with the local farmers in the region. Data was collected directly from the farmers through semi-structured interview using a questionnaire based on the input requirements of the ecoinvent LCI calculation tool for crop production. The farmers do not maintain any written records and have provided the data from recent memory. In this region, typically farmers are unable to provide exact name of active ingredient in the pesticide they use and the same was noted from details given on the pesticide packet. Individual farmer is not able to calculate fuel consumption for his own farm alone and this information has been collected from farming community of the area.</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">Ecoinvent LCI calculation tool for crop production was used to calculate field emissions from the cultivation process. Number of wet days have been taken for neighboring district (Ludhiana) and rainfall data is Normal rainfall for Punjab State in India where the farm is located. The data has been approximated using Wheat as proxy since the tool at this stage could not support non existing crops in ecoeditor.</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
